<item>
            <title>[SEC-801] Coudl not create a new AuthorizationException and add it to the exceptionMappings</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-801</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It seems it is not possible to create additional exceptions that extends AuthenticationException and register them in the exceptionMappings Properties variable contained in org.acegisecurity.ui.AbstractProcessingFilter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Seems that doAddExtraDefaultExceptionMappings(Properties exceptionMappings) method is protected and it is not implemented (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.jdocs.com/acegi/1.0.0/org/acegisecurity/providers/ProviderManager.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.jdocs.com/acegi/1.0.0/org/acegisecurity/providers/ProviderManager.html&lt;/a&gt;) in org.acegisecurity.providers.ProviderManager. Then, it obligates you to use one of the default Exceptions loaded in its afterPropertiesSet().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>I am using Acegi 1.0.0 and could not try the last version (Spring Security). The method that has the bug got deprecated in the new version (Deprecated. This method has been removed from the 2.0 series; please use the ProviderManager.additionalExceptionMappings property instead to inject additional exception to event mappings ).</environment>
